  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary objective of this study is to evaluate gastric volume and contents as well as
      gall bladder size in patients scheduled for routine, urgent, and emergency surgery. The
      hypothesis is that patients with stress, pain and opioid administration will have delayed
      gastric emptying and therefore a larger gastric fluid volume than those scheduled for
      elective surgery. The patients who have an appropriate NPO time will have a larger
      gallbladder size than the patients with shorter NPO time.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
